# Trivy ignore-list — entries here are scanned but do NOT fail CI.
#
# Every line MUST be either a comment (`#`) or a single vulnerability ID
# (CVE-…, GHSA-…). Each accepted exception MUST be cross-referenced to a
# finding in docs/security/audit-report.md so the residual risk has an
# owner and a tracking issue. When a fix becomes available (Next.js
# upgrade, Debian point release, etc.) the corresponding ID MUST be
# removed from this file so the CI gate ratchets back up.
#
# Re-run the scanners locally before editing:
#   trivy fs . --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --ignore-unfixed
#   trivy image tgai-backend:security-scan --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --ignore-unfixed

